com.camerontec.util.jmx.cascading.managedhosts

Class ManagedHost

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.jmx.cascading.managedhosts.ManagedHost
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IManagedHost

    public class ManagedHost
extends Object
implements IManagedHost
    Instances of this class represent hosts managed by the MA.
    A ManagedHost basically consists in a host name (or an IP address) and the JMX service URL of the LMA running on this host.
    Instances constructed with a null JMX service URL will be assumed to be using the default JMX service URL, which is service:jmx:jmxmp://<host>:10002, where <host> represents the host name (or IP address).
    Author:
    guillaume.jacob@orcsoftware.com

      • ManagedHost

        public ManagedHost()
        Constructor. Creates a new managed host with a null host name, JMX Service URL and security profile.

      • ManagedHost

        public ManagedHost(String hostName,
                   String jmxServiceURL,
                   JMXTLSClientProfile securityProfile)
            throws MalformedURLException,
                   InvalidHostNameInJMXServiceURLException
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        hostName - the name or IP address of the managed host
        jmxServiceURL - the string representation of the JMX service URL of the LMA running on this managed host - if null, then the default JMX service URL (service:jmx:jmxmp://<host>:10002) will be assumed
        securityProfile - the security profile associated with the host
        Throws:
        MalformedURLException - if jmxServiceURL is not a valid representation of a JMX service URL
        InvalidHostNameInJMXServiceURLException - if the host name part in the JMX service URL represented by jmxServiceURL is not strictly equal to hostName (regardless of any IP address / host name resolution)
